definition: mark/sign/label/to mark with a symbol, label, lettering etc/to bear (a brand name, registration number etc)/prize/award/bid/target/quota/(old) the topmost branches of a tree/visible symptom/classifier for military units
tree/wood/coffin/wooden/simple/numb/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]
to cross the limit/to be over the accepted norm/excessive
variant of 標誌|标志[biao1 zhi4]

sentences.english: The hurricane last night destroyed many survey markers.
sentences.chinese: 昨晚台风摧毁了很多觇标。

sentences.english: Markets see-sawed all day, with S&P officials refusing to comment on their plans.
sentences.chinese: 市场全天反复涨跌，标普高管拒绝就其计划置评。

sentences.english: Applications for building permits, an indicator of future construction activity, also fell.
sentences.chinese: 建房申请，也是未来建筑活动的指向标，也在下降。

sentences.english: Waterlogged and alkaline areas were marked down for special attention.
sentences.chinese: 易涝地区和碱地都标了出来，以便特别注意。

sentences.english: Aim The method of designing the luminous intensity distribution of aerodrome beacon was analyzed and investigated.
sentences.chinese: 分析和研究机场标灯光强角度分布的设计方法。

sentences.english: As you can see, people advertise disproportionately high salaries for themselves.
sentences.chinese: 可以看到，人们都在给自己标上不相称的高工资。

sentences.english: Conclusion Standard diagnoses at present has advantage in diagnosing MCLS in young children at the early time.
sentences.chinese: 结论按照目前诊断标，有利于早期诊断小儿MCLS。

sentences.english: Click on the square icon to maximize the window.
sentences.chinese: 点击方框图标，使窗口最大化。

sentences.english: The compression ratios were noted from individual products' log files.
sentences.chinese: 压缩比是从单个产品的日志文件标记录出来的。

sentences.english: Make sure you use a hard surface and wait for the yolk to settle.
sentences.chinese: 记得要找坚硬标材质的表面，要等到蛋黄沉下来再立。

sentences.english: This type of performance data collection kills two birds with one stone.
sentences.chinese: 这种性能数据收集方法可以一箭双标。

sentences.english: All these ancient books and paintings have been marked up.
sentences.chinese: 所有这些古书古画都标了价。

sentences.english: This paper analyses the systematic error of three coordinate measuring machine of bridge type construction.
sentences.chinese: 本文分析了桥式三座标测量机的系统误差。

sentences.english: Booth : He's got no sense of discretion. That kid. Typical squint.
sentences.chinese: 那孩儿点儿正常判断力没有，标标准准的眯眼。

sentences.english: The calculation of characters of group representation is the basis of studying the irreducible representation of groups.
sentences.chinese: 计算各种群的特征标，是研究群不可约表示的基础。

definition: variant of 標誌|标志[biao1 zhi4]
to mark out/to tag/to put a sign on sth explaining or calling attention to/to annotate (e.g. a character with its pinyin)
model or template character/written slogan or phrase/mention (e.g. "air mail" 航空 on a letter, "first draft" 初稿 on a document etc)
to control/to accuse/to charge/to sue/to invert a container to empty it/(suffix) (slang) buff/enthusiast/devotee/-phile or -philia
